        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued November 19 at 7:13PM MST by NWS Phoenix AZ</headline>
        <description>At 712 PM MST, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Salt River Indian Community, or near Fountain Hills, moving northeast
at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mesa, Scottsdale, Fountain Hills, Paradise Valley, Sugarloaf
Mountain, Granite Reef Dam, McDowell Mountain Park, Salt River Indian
Community, Rio Verde, Goldfield Ranch, and Fort McDowell.

This includes the following highways...
AZ Route 87 between mile markers 179 and 194, and near mile marker
206.
AZ Route 202 between mile markers 15 and 21.
AZ Route 101 between mile markers 39 and 47.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
